Document: GLTFSkin
Path: godot/classes/class_gltfskin.rst
Summary: Defines the properties of a GLTFSkin object, which represents a skinning armature in a glTF scene.

Properties:
- godot_skin (Skin): The Godot Skin resource associated with this GLTFSkin.
- joints (PackedInt32Array): An array of bone indices that form the joints of the skin.
- joints_original (PackedInt32Array): An array of original bone indices, used for mapping.
- non_joints (PackedInt32Array): An array of node indices that are not joints but are part of the skinning hierarchy.
- roots (PackedInt32Array): An array of root node indices for each skin.
- skeleton (int): The index of the skeleton node in the glTF scene. Default: -1.
- skin_root (int): The index of the root node of the skin in the glTF scene. Default: -1.
---CHUNK---
Document: GLTFSkin
Path: godot/classes/class_gltfskin.rst
Summary: Provides methods for accessing and modifying skinning data within a GLTF model.
Method: get_inverse_binds() → Array[Transform3D]
Returns the inverse bind matrices for the skin.
Method: get_joint_i_to_bone_i() → Dictionary
Returns a dictionary mapping joint indices to bone indices.
Method: get_joint_i_to_name() → Dictionary
Returns a dictionary mapping joint indices to bone names.
Method: set_inverse_binds(inverse_binds: Array[Transform3D]) → void
Sets the inverse bind matrices for the skin.
Method: set_joint_i_to_bone_i(joint_i_to_bone_i: Dictionary) → void
Sets the mapping from joint indices to bone indices.
Method: set_joint_i_to_name(joint_i_to_name: Dictionary) → void
Sets the mapping from joint indices to bone names.
---CHUNK---
